const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Why does Schott Ceran inner pane glass take 4 to 6 weeks to source?",
    a: "Schott Ceran is the German-manufactured ceramic glass used as the inner pane on Wolf, Miele, Thermador, and Gaggenau wall oven doors. The pane is brand-specific and generation-specific, sourced through the manufacturer's authorized parts network in Europe, with import lead time of 4 to 6 weeks standard. Generic ceramic glass with a different thermal expansion coefficient cracks again within months because the heat-cycle stress profile doesn't match the door frame. We use authorized OEM only on these.",
  },
  {
    q: "Should I replace both pairs of hinges on my double oven proactively?",
    a: "Yes, on most GE, KitchenAid, and Whirlpool double wall ovens past year 8. The lower oven hinges fail 3 to 4 years before the upper because the lower cavity sees more heat (rising heat from below cycles compounds), more weight on the door, and more open-close cycles in everyday use. By the time the lower hinges sag, the upper are 60 to 80% along the same wear curve. Replacing both pairs in one visit costs $120 to $200 extra in parts but saves a full second service call within 12 to 24 months.",
  },
