    q: "Pro-tier hinges (Wolf, Miele, Thermador) cost?",
    a: "Heavy-duty spring assemblies running $600 to $900 per pair vs $200 to $380 mid-tier. Worth it because pro-tier doors are designed for 18 to 25 year service life; replacing hinges at year 10 to 12 keeps the rest of the unit on its design curve. We see pro-tier hinges still functioning at year 18 in Beverly Hills and Bel Air kitchens.",
  },
  {
    q: "My wall oven door light is always on. Why?",
    a: "Door switch fault. The small mechanical switch that detects door open or closed has stuck in the open-detected position. Light is the obvious symptom; the bigger issue is the safety interlock typically uses the same switch, so the oven might also refuse to start (board reads door always open). Replacement runs $200 to $340 mid-tier, $340 to $540 pro-tier.",
  },
  {
    q: "Door gasket compressed, can I just replace it myself?",
    a: "Mid-tier gasket replacement is doable for a handy homeowner; the gasket usually clips into the door perimeter without specialty tools. Pro-tier German doors (Wolf, Miele, Thermador, Gaggenau) use brand-specific gasket profiles that require door panel removal and authorized-parts sourcing. Mid-tier $80 to $180 DIY part. Pro-tier $260 to $480 with our service plus access labor.",
  },
