<!-- 05 BRAND NOTES -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">05 · Brand-specific door notes</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What's distinct on each brand.</h2>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Wolf E-series.</strong> Stainless front panel mounting different from sheet-metal mid-tier; door panel removal requires authorized procedure. Schott Ceran inner pane on most generations. Sub-Zero Group authorized parts pipeline.</li>
      <li><strong>Miele PureLine.</strong> Continuous one-piece door gasket profile (not multi-piece). German parts pipeline 5 to 7 days standard, longer for inner pane glass. M Touch and M Pro variants share door hardware.</li>
      <li><strong>Thermador Professional.</strong> Door hinge spring assemblies are heavy-duty stainless. BSH Group authorized service. Inner pane Schott Ceran on Pro-Series.</li>
      <li><strong>Gaggenau BO and BS.</strong> Premium tier above Thermador (same BSH parent). German parts often longer lead time, we confirm at diagnostic.</li>
      <li><strong>GE Monogram.</strong> Premium GE built-in. Door hardware platform distinct from GE Profile.</li>
      <li><strong>GE Profile, KitchenAid Architect, Whirlpool, JennAir.</strong> Mid-tier built-in cluster. Whirlpool family (KitchenAid, JennAir, Whirlpool) shares door hinge platforms across most generations; GE Profile separate. Double-oven lower-fails-first pattern strongest on this cluster.</li>
      <li><strong>Bosch and Samsung.</strong> Mid-tier built-in entrants. Bosch Benchmark series sits above standard 800-series with heavier door hardware.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 06 WHY US -->
